<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>22-3020.51</num>
  <heading>Definitions.</heading>
  <text>For the purposes of this subchapter, the term:</text>
  <para>
    <num>(1)</num>
    <text>“Child” means an individual who has not yet attained the age of 16 years.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(2)</num>
    <text>“Person” means an individual 18 years of age or older.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(3)</num>
    <text>“Police” means the Metropolitan Police Department.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(4)</num>
    <text>“Sexual abuse” means any act that is a violation of:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(A)</num>
      <text>Section 22-1834;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(B)</num>
      <text>Section <cite path="§22-2704">§ 22-2704</cite>;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(C)</num>
      <text>This chapter (<cite path="§22-3001">§ 22-3001</cite> et seq.); or</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(D)</num>
      <text>Section 22-3102.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
